    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my blueberry bushes are starting to look kinda weird. the leaves are turning yellow but the veins are still green. do u think its a nitrogen problem or is the soil ph just messed up?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves with green veins in blueberry bushes are a classic sign of a few different issues, and it's not just one thing. It could be a nitrogen deficiency, but it could also be a pH imbalance, which can make it hard for the plant to absorb the nutrients even if they are present.\n\nYou should check your soil pH first, as that's a big one. If the pH is too high or too low, the plant can't get the nitrogen it needs, even if you've fertilized. A soil test is the best way to know for sure, though.",
      "source": "target",
